This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image filtering. The use of reservoir computing, a type of neural network, suggests that it could also belong to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. The paper also discusses the possibility of implementing these networks in hardware, which could place it in the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the use of inverse modeling suggests that it could belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the use of machine learning techniques for image filtering could also place it in the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
